PHONE_REDACTEDT16:PORT:PORT.171769Z	   21 Query	insert into daily_analysis_reports (analysis_confidence,analysis_scope_note,day,executive_summary,generated_at,misconfiguration_signals,system_behavior_analysis,user_behavior_analysis) values ('Analysis confidence is medium due to the absence of rate limit failures by final page, which could be indicative of additional system constraints.','This analysis is based on one calendar day''s data (PHONE_REDACTED) and focuses only on backend lead submission behavior.','PHONE_REDACTED','On the PHONE_REDACTED (IST), there were a total of 206 lead submissions, with a success ratio of 63.59%. Notably, duplicate leads accounted for 70 failed attempts, and rate limit exceedances occurred 5 times.','PHONE_REDACTED:PORT:PORT.167274','The high number of duplicate leads may indicate a potential configuration issue with lead validation or storage.','Leads were primarily submitted via the website form (200 attempts), with only one submission from the funnel page. The system''s maximum attempts per minute were recorded as 17, and there were no burst minutes.','The users with the highest activity were EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED, who made 101 and 102 attempts respectively. Both users experienced a failure ratio over 40%.')
